Q1:
We would like to thank you in advance for participating in our survey, since this helps us to proceed with our research.
We're conducting research on what the difference is in effect of cyberloafing on employee productivity across Generation X, Y and Z. The definition of cyberloafing entails being at work and using internet for personal, non-work related purposes.We'd love to hear from you about your experiences about cyberloafing and productivity, which will be the main topics of this questionnaire. This will help us make improvements to existing literature and help policy workers related to this topic. The survey should take about 7 minutes, and your responses are completely anonymous.
If you consent you allow us to use your information for our research project only, only the teacher and students in the group will use this information. Participation is completely voluntary and if you decide that you do not want to participate anymore you may stop at any point in the survey. All participants must be at least 18 years of age or otherwise have permission from their parents to make this survey.
If you have any question you can contact us at y.j.m.laheij@student.vu.nl
